A D.C. woman has been assigned a medical guardian after making thousands of calls to 911 over three decades and being its most frequent user.

Superior Court Judge Erik P. Christian approved the move on Monday for Martha Rigsby, The Washington Post reports. Christian called Rigsby's calls a 'serial, excessive and unwarranted' burden on the city's emergency services.

It is thought to be the first case in which city officials have tried to limit a 911 user.

