Rigbsy, 59, was known in the 1980s as 'Metro Martha,' the paper reports, because she frequently fell at D.C. Metro stations. She usually suffered seizures or fainting spells.

A fire department official told the paper in November 2013 that Rigsby was linked to at least 226 calls to 911 and 117 ambulance trips in the past twelve months.

According to that report, Rigsby owes $61,366.33 to D.C. Fire and EMS for ambulance rides. Each trip in the past five years averaged $478.

Since then, she has taken approximately 30 ambulance trips.

